vider API.","react application"]}]},{"name":"newNotebook","description":"Create a new Jupyter Notebook","sampleRequest":"How do I create a notebook to load data from a csv file?","disambiguation":[{"category":"create_jupyter_notebook","description":"The user wants to create a new Jupyter notebook in Visual Studio Code.","examples":["Create a notebook to analyze this CSV file."]}]},{"name":"setupTests","description":"Set up tests in your project (Experimental)","sampleRequest":"add playwright tests to my project","when":"config.github.copilot.chat.setupTests.enabled","disambiguation":[{"category":"set_up_tests","description":"The user wants to configure project test setup, framework, or test runner. The user does not want to fix their existing tests.","examples":["Set up tests for this project."]}]}],"disambiguation":[]},"modelId":"copilot/auto","responseId":"response_9a9d7a23-ed77-48ff-a3bb-4bcf6033db89","result":{"timings":{"firstProgress":13566,"totalElapsed":16233},"metadata":{"codeBlocks":[],"toolCallRounds":[{"response":"This file is a JSONC configuration for a bar/status system, probably something like Waybar. The first object defines the global layout and which modules appear in each section of the bar.\n\nAt the top level, the bar is placed on the “top” layer and “top” position, with a 10-pixel top margin and a width of 1000 pixels. The left part of the bar contains the `hyprland/workspaces` module, the center contains the `clock` module, and the right side contains `network`, `pulseaudio`, and `battery`.\n\nThe second object contains per-module settings. The `clock` module is configured with an alternate format string showing day of week, day, month, and time. The `pulseaudio` module has a default volume format, a Bluetooth-specific format, a muted icon format, and a mapping of device types to icons. It also defines a click action to open `pavucontrol` and ignores a sink named “Easy Effects Sink”.\n\nThe `network` module is set to monitor interface `enp6s0`. It has different display formats for wired and wireless connections, and it hides itself completely when disconnected by using an empty `format-disconnected`. It also customizes tooltip text for different states and limits the displayed text to 50 characters.\n\nThe `hyprland/workspaces` module is intended to define how workspace names are displayed, and `persistent-workspaces` is used to keep up to five workspaces across sessions.\n\nThe excerpt also contains syntax issues: there is an extra closing brace after the first object, a trailing comma after the `battery` module list, and the `format` value for `hyprland/workspaces` is missing its closing quote and closing brace. Those mistakes would prevent the JSONC from parsing correctly until fixed.","toolCalls":[],"toolInputRetry":0,"id":"391bd39f-3667-46c5-b0b6-da612eea8f63","statefulMarker":"","thinking":{"id":"","text":"**Analyzing configuration objects**\n\nI'm looking at a top-level object that defines various settings, like layer, position, margin, and width, plus module arrays. The modules include things like workspaces, a clock, network info, PulseAudio, and battery status. There's also a second object for specific module settings, but it seems to have formatting issues, like missing a closing quote and brace. It might be better to merge this into the first object since it's causing invalid configuration. I need to explain this clearly without using markdown.","encrypted":"","tokens":256},"timestamp":1777741606324}],"resolvedModel":"capi-noe-ptuc-h200-oswe-vscode-prime","modelMessageId":"a99896a5-b3bc-48fa-8557-9c0f8b53f906","responseId":"bdce1d81-6814-45cb-a9b6-f44f4ef20e0d","sessionId":"8284d764-3ee7-42ab-bb1a-e7953a215f91","agentId":"github.copilot.editsAgent","command":"explain"},"details":"Raptor mini (Preview) • 1x"},"responseMarkdownInfo":[],"followups":[],"modelState":{"value":1,"completedAt":1777741606333},"slashCommand":{"name":"explain","description":"Explain how the code in your active editor wo