nd time. The `pulseaudio` module has a default volume format, a Bluetooth-specific format, a muted icon format, and a mapping of device types to icons. It also defines a click action to open `pavucontrol` and ignores a sink named “Easy Effects Sink”.\n\nThe `network` module is set to monitor interface `enp6s0`. It has different display formats for wired and wireless connections, and it hides itself completely when disconnected by using an empty `format-disconnected`. It also customizes tooltip text for different states and limits the displayed text to 50 characters.\n\nThe `hyprland/workspaces` module is intended to define how workspace names are displayed, and `persistent-workspaces` is used to keep up to five workspaces across sessions.\n\nThe excerpt also contains syntax issues: there is an extra closing brace after the first object, a trailing comma after the `battery` module list, and the `format` value for `hyprland/workspaces` is missing its closing quote and closing brace. Those mistakes would prevent the JSONC from parsing correctly until fixed.","supportThemeIcons":false,"supportHtml":false,"baseUri":{"$mid":1,"path":"/home/chris/.config/waybar/","scheme":"file"}}],"message":{"text":"/explain ","parts":[{"range":{"start":0,"endExclusive":8},"editorRange":{"startLineNumber":1,"startColumn":1,"endLineNumber":1,"endColumn":9},"command":{"name":"explain","description":"Explain how the code in your active editor works"},"kind":"subcommand"},{"range":{"start":8,"endExclusive":9},"editorRange":{"startLineNumber":1,"startColumn":9,"endLineNumber":1,"endColumn":10},"text":" ","kind":"text"}]},"variableData":{"variables":[]}}]}
